Package com.simulation.database

Class SimulationResultsDAO

java.lang.Object
com.simulation.database.SimulationResultsDAO
public class SimulationResultsDAO extends Object
Data Access Object (DAO) for SimulationResults.

This class provides database operations for persisting simulation run results, including:

  • Creating new simulation run records
  • Updating run results with statistics
  • Saving individual task data
  • Querying historical simulation runs

Database Tables:

  • simulation_runs: Stores overall run metadata and statistics
  • simulation_tasks: Stores individual task details
Version:
2.0
Author:
Cloud Simulation Team

  • Method Details

    • createSimulationRun

      public int createSimulationRun(Integer configId, String runName) throws SQLException
      Creates a new simulation run record in the database.

      This method inserts a new row into the simulation_runs table with initial status 'RUNNING'. The run can be associated with a saved configuration by providing a configId, or can be standalone (configId = null).

      Parameters:
      configId - the ID of the associated configuration, or null if none
      runName - a descriptive name for this simulation run
      Returns:
      the auto-generated run_id, or -1 if creation failed
      Throws:
      SQLException - if a database access error occurs

    • updateSimulationRun

      public boolean updateSimulationRun(int runId, SimulationResults results, String status) throws SQLException
      Updates a simulation run with final results and statistics.

      This method is called when the simulation completes. It updates the run record with final statistics including duration, task counts, average system time, throughput, and final status (COMPLETED or FAILED).

      Parameters:
      runId - the ID of the simulation run to update
      results - the SimulationResults containing final statistics
      status - the final status ('COMPLETED', 'FAILED', 'STOPPED')
      Returns:
      true if update was successful, false otherwise
      Throws:
      SQLException - if a database access error occurs
